TITLE: Initializing Server Data with Meteor.startup (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use Meteor.startup on the server to initialize data in a collection if it's empty. It checks the count of items in the LinksCollection and inserts a new item if the collection is empty.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/v3-docs/docs/api/meteor.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { Meteor } from "meteor/meteor";
import { LinksCollection } from "/imports/api/links";

Meteor.startup(async () => {
  // If the Links collection is empty, add some data.
  if ((await LinksCollection.find().countAsync()) === 0) {
    await LinksCollection.insertAsync({
      title: "Do the Tutorial",
      url: "https://www.meteor.com/tutorials/react/creating-an-app",
    });
  }
});
```

