TITLE: Publishing Related Data Sets with Meteor in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates publishing multiple datasets in a single publication, using both the primary and related datasets from the Todos and Lists collections. The publication validates listId and checks user permissions before returning cursors. It will return an empty ready state if the user is unauthorized. The appropriate schema validation and authentication mechanisms must be set up in your Meteor application.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/guide/source/data-loading.md#2025-04-22_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
Meteor.publish('todos.inList', function(listId) {
  new SimpleSchema({
    listId: {type: String}
  }).validate({ listId });

  const list = Lists.findOne(listId);

  if (list && (!list.userId || list.userId === this.userId)) {
    return [
      Lists.find(listId),
      Todos.find({listId})
    ];
  } else {
    return this.ready();
  }
});
```

