TITLE: Registering Cleanup Logic on Computation Invalidation using Tracker.onInvalidate in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to check if code is running inside a Tracker computation (`Tracker.active`). If so, it registers a callback using `Tracker.onInvalidate` that executes cleanup functions (`x.destroy()`, `y.finalize()`) when the current computation is either invalidated (about to be rerun) or stopped. This pattern is useful for managing resources tied to a reactive computation's lifecycle.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/v3-docs/docs/api/Tracker.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
// If we're in a computation, then perform some clean-up when the current
// computation is invalidated (rerun or stopped).
if (Tracker.active) {
  Tracker.onInvalidate(() => {
    x.destroy();
    y.finalize();
  });
}
```

