TITLE: Implementing a Secure Todo Update Method in Meteor
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows a Meteor method for updating todo text. It includes validation, permission checking using this.userId, and demonstrates proper error handling in Meteor methods.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/guide/source/accounts.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
Meteor.methods({
  'todos.updateText'({ todoId, newText }) {
    new SimpleSchema({
      todoId: { type: String },
      newText: { type: String }
    }).validate({ todoId, newText }),

    const todo = Todos.findOne(todoId);

    if (!todo.editableBy(this.userId)) {
      throw new Meteor.Error('todos.updateText.unauthorized',
        'Cannot edit todos in a private list that is not yours');
    }

    Todos.update(todoId, {
      $set: { text: newText }
    });
  }
});
```

