TITLE: Comparing Meteor Collection `find().fetch()` vs `find({selector}).fetch()` (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Contrasts two approaches for processing collection data within a `Tracker.autorun`. Version 1 fetches all posts (`Posts.find().fetch()`) and filters in JavaScript, causing reruns on any change to any post. Version 2 uses a selector (`Posts.find({tag:"kittens"}).fetch()`) to fetch only relevant posts, making the autorun react only to changes in posts tagged 'kittens', demonstrating more efficient, fine-grained reactivity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/docs/long-form/tracker-manual.md#2025-04-22_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```js
// VERSION 1 (INEFFICIENT)
Tracker.autorun(function(){
  var allPosts = Posts.find().fetch();
