TITLE: Sharing Meteor Accounts Across Servers via DDP
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates authenticating a user on a second Meteor server (B) using the resume token obtained from the first server (A). Requires both servers to share the same database and uses `DDP.connect()` to establish a connection and a separate `AccountsClient` instance to log in with the token. The code runs on server A.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/guide/source/structure.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
// This is server A's token as the default `Accounts` points at our server
const token = Accounts._storedLoginToken();

// We create a *second* accounts client pointing at server B
const app2 = DDP.connect('url://of.server.b');
const accounts2 = new AccountsClient({ connection: app2 });

// Now we can login with the token. Further calls to `accounts2` will be authenticated
accounts2.loginWithToken(token);
```

