TITLE: Efficient List Rendering with useFind and React Memoization - JavaScript/JSX
DESCRIPTION: This snippet integrates useFind with React.memo to optimize list rendering based on Mongo queries using Meteor. It demonstrates memoizing list items and observing only relevant data changes for fine-grained reactivity. Dependencies are meteor/react-meteor-data, a valid Mongo collection, and React. The useFind hook takes a cursor factory and dependencies; output is an array of documents with stable references. Caution: do not call .fetch() in useFind to maintain reference integrity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/v3-docs/docs/packages/react-meteor-data.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

