TITLE: Comparing Meteor `fetch().length` vs `cursor.count()` for Reactivity (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Compares calculating the number of documents matching a query within a `Tracker.autorun`. Version 1 uses `fetch().length`, which depends on the actual documents and reruns if any matching document is added, removed, or *edited*. Version 2 uses `cursor.count()`, which depends only on the *number* of matching documents, making it more efficient as it only reruns when documents are added or removed, not merely edited.
