TITLE: Synchronizing Async Tracker Autoruns via firstRunPromise in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This example illustrates awaiting the `firstRunPromise` property returned by `Tracker.autorun` when using an async function. This allows sequential execution, ensuring the first autorun's initial asynchronous operations (like `Meteor.userAsync()`) complete before the next `await` statement or subsequent `autorun` begins. It's a way to manually synchronize the startup of reactive computations involving async operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/v3-docs/docs/api/Tracker.md#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
await Tracker.autorun(async () => {
  await Meteor.userAsync();
  (...more async code...)
}).firstRunPromise;

await Tracker.autorun(async () => {
  await asyncSomeOrOther();
  (...more async code...)
}).firstRunPromise;
```

