TITLE: Implementing Publication Security with Roles in Meteor
DESCRIPTION: Example of a Meteor publication using role-based access control to publish secret documents. It checks if the user has 'view-secrets' or 'admin' role in the specified scope before publishing the documents.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/v3-docs/docs/packages/roles.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// server/publications.js
Meteor.publish("secretDocuments", async function (scope) {
  check(scope, String);

  const canView = await Roles.userIsInRoleAsync(
    this.userId,
    ["view-secrets", "admin"],
    scope
  );

  if (canView) {
    return SecretDocs.find({ scope: scope });
  }

  this.ready();
});
```

