TITLE: Hydrating Vuex Store on Client-Side for SSR (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the client-side hydration process in a Meteor-Vue SSR setup. Within `Meteor.startup`, it retrieves the initial state (`window.__INITIAL_STATE__`) embedded in the HTML by the server and uses `store.replaceState()` to initialize the Vuex store, ensuring consistency between server-rendered content and the client-side application state. Requires a Vuex store instance and assumes `window.__INITIAL_STATE__` is populated by the server.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/guide/source/vue.md#2025-04-22_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { Meteor } from 'meteor/meteor';
import createApp from './app';

Meteor.startup(() => {
  const { store, router } = createApp({ // Same function as the server
    ssr: false,
  });

  // Hydrate the Vuex store with the JSON string
  if (window.__INITIAL_STATE__) {
    store.replaceState(window.__INITIAL_STATE__);
  }
});
```

