TITLE: Custom Collection Insert Method in Meteor
DESCRIPTION: Example of extending Mongo.Collection to create a custom insert method that automatically generates unique list names before insertion. Demonstrates schema validation and document initialization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/guide/source/collections.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class ListsCollection extends Mongo.Collection {
  insert(list, callback) {
    if (!list.name) {
      let nextLetter = 'A';
      list.name = `List ${nextLetter}`;

      while (!!this.findOne({name: list.name})) {
        // not going to be too smart here, can't go past Z
        nextLetter = String.fromCharCode(nextLetter.charCodeAt(0) + 1);
        list.name = `List ${nextLetter}`;
      }
    }

    // Call the original `insert` method, which will validate
    // against the schema
    return super.insert(list, callback);
  }
}

Lists = new ListsCollection('lists');
```

