TITLE: Setting Custom Error Messages for Rate-Limit Rules in DDPRateLimiter (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to define a new rate-limit rule and associate a custom error message with it in DDPRateLimiter. The example focuses on limiting Google Authenticator setups, accommodating one attempt per minute, providing a user-friendly feedback mechanism by displaying a customized error message. Necessary prerequisites include adding the ddp-rate-limiter package and having valid user data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/v3-docs/docs/api/DDPRateLimiter.md#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const setupGoogleAuthenticatorRule = {
  userId(userId) {
    const user = Meteor.users.findOne(userId);
    return user;
  },
  type: 'method',
  name: 'Users.setupGoogleAuthenticator',
};

// Add the rule, allowing up to 1 google auth setup message every 60 seconds
const ruleId = DDPRateLimiter.addRule(setupGoogleAuthenticatorRule, 1, 60000);
DDPRateLimiter.setErrorMessageOnRule(ruleId, function (data) {
  return `You have reached the maximum number of Google Authenticator attempts. Please try again in ${Math.ceil(data.timeToReset / 1000)} seconds.`;
});
```

