TITLE: Requiring Magic Square Row, Column, and Diagonal Sums with Logic Solver in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Expresses the constraints that every row, column, and diagonal in the magic square must sum to 15. This is achieved by calling solver.require with Logic.equalBits on all relevant triplets. Prerequisites: a Logic.Solver instance, a defined list of 4-bit variables and the 'fifteen' bits. Input: groups of three variables; Output: constraints added to the solver. Implicitly, runs for all line groupings relevant to magic squares.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/packages/logic-solver/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
var solver = new Logic.Solver();

_.each([[A,B,C], [D,E,F], [G,H,I], [A,D,G], [B,E,H], [C,F,I],
        [A,E,I], [G,E,C]],
       function (terms) {
         solver.require(Logic.equalBits(Logic.sum(terms), fifteen));
       });
```

