TITLE: Default Placeholder Replacement Logic in meteor generate (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Displays the default JavaScript `transformName` function used internally by `meteor generate`. This function replaces placeholders (`$$name$$`, `$$PascalName$$`, `$$camelName$$`) in template file names and contents based on the provided scaffold name (`scaffoldName`), converting it to PascalCase and camelCase using helper functions (`toPascalCase`, `toCamelCase`).
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/v3-docs/docs/cli/index.md#2025-04-22_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
const transformName = (name) => {
    return name.replace(/\$\$name\$\$|\$\$PascalName\$\$|\$\$camelName\$\$/g, function (substring, args) {
      if (substring === '$$name$$') return scaffoldName;
      if (substring === '$$PascalName$$') return toPascalCase(scaffoldName);
      if (substring === '$$camelName$$') return toCamelCase(scaffoldName);
    })
  }
```

