TITLE: Adding Range Constraints to Each Magic Square Location with Logic Solver in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Adds new requirements such that each digit variable must take values between 1 and 9 inclusive. Calls solver.require for both greaterThanOrEqual and lessThanOrEqual constraints per location, then solves again to ensure all digits are within range. Outputs: valid magic square where all values are 1-9.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/packages/logic-solver/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
_.each(locations, function (loc) {
  solver.require(Logic.greaterThanOrEqual(loc, Logic.constantBits(1)));
  solver.require(Logic.lessThanOrEqual(loc, Logic.constantBits(9)));
});

var sol2 = solver.solve();
_.map(locations, function (loc) { return sol2.evaluate(loc); })
// => [8, 1, 6,
//     3, 5, 7,
//     4, 9, 2]
```

