TITLE: Adding Middleware to Submodule | meteor-rpc | TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates attaching a middleware function to a submodule using addMiddlewares. This middleware logs a message before the method handler runs. Middleware functions receive 'raw' and 'parsed' arguments, supporting effects like logging or validation. Middleware ordering is stack-based (last in, first out).
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/v3-docs/docs/community-packages/meteor-rpc.md#2025-04-22_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { ChatCollection } from "/imports/api/chat";
import { createModule } from "meteor-rpc";

export const chatModule = createModule("chat")
  .addMiddlewares([
    (raw, parsed) => {
      console.log("runs first");
    },
  ])
  .addMethod("createChat", z.void(), async () => {
    return ChatCollection.insertAsync({ createdAt: new Date(), messages: [] });
  })
  .buildSubmodule();
```

