TITLE: Parsing Triple-Slash Documentation Comments
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the use of triple-slash (`///`) comments, often used for documentation. An optional single space immediately following the `///` sequence is removed by the parser. Multiple consecutive lines starting with `///` are concatenated to form a single documentation comment block, treated as one paragraph. Separate sequences of `///` comments result in distinct paragraphs.
