TITLE: Using throwStubExceptions Option in Meteor Method Calls
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the new throwStubExceptions option when calling Meteor methods, which allows exceptions from method stubs to be thrown instead of logged.
SOURCE: https://github.com/meteor/meteor/blob/devel/docs/history.md#2025-04-22_snippet_90

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
Meteor.call('methodName', arg1, arg2, { throwStubExceptions: true }, callback)
```
